http://www.ece.sunysb.edu/~zyweng/dpcluster.html
An implmentation of sampling for DPMM using CRP.

http://cs.brown.edu/~sudderth/papers/sudderthPhD.pdf
Chapter 2 of Sudderths PhD thesis has a good explanation for clustering via DPMMs and sampling strategies.

http://xiaodong-yu.blogspot.ca/2009/09/gibbs-sampling-for-dp-mixtures.html
Explanation of Neal's paper

http://www.cc.gatech.edu/~jscholz6/resources/presentations//Tutorials%20&%20Presentations/Scholz,%20J.,%20(9-2-11)%20DP%20tutorial%20part%202%20(Pfunk%20Lab%20meeting).pdf
Insightful representation of cluster analysis using DPMM and comparison to EM

References for Chinese Restaurant Process:
https://www.cs.princeton.edu/courses/archive/fall07/cos597C/scribe/20070921.pdf
http://web.cse.ohio-state.edu/~kulis/teaching/788_sp12/scribe_notes/lecture13.pdf
http://blog.datumbox.com/the-dirichlet-process-the-chinese-restaurant-process-and-other-representations/

and a fast and intuition friendly (!) tutorial on all of these processes:
http://blog.echen.me/2012/03/20/infinite-mixture-models-with-nonparametric-bayes-and-the-dirichlet-process/


